iak guards at the arena in Lake Rathetear with my mage and warrior friend.<br>
<br>
I would periodically log off, switch to my enchanter, log on and buff the two of them. (Mage and pet with a shield, clarity and gift of magic for Mage.  Augment, shield and Rune 3 for the warrior).  Well, I decided that I'm a bad ass level 21 rogue, I can kill a puny level 18 warrior.<br>
<br>
I challenge him to a dual, completely forgetting the buffs he had, we pulled another guard, then I remembered Rune 3, I let the guard beat the Rune 3 off of him, then we finished it off, he then accepted the dual (I had still forgotten about the other handy buffs, obscure and augment.<br>
<br>
Well, he accepts and the fight is on, first thing I do is jump at him and mouse look in mid-air to turn around for the backstab (gotta love counter strike for teaching me that one.) Too late, he ran forward to get away from me (he knows I love to jump over him repeatedly so he can't see me to invite me to a group, he also knows about back stab.)<br>
<br>
Well, the fight goes on, and we are actually doing about the same damage to each other, I landed about 3 backstabs (for about half normal damage).  My bloodclaw proc'ed, he resisted, it proc'ed again, it stuck.  Finally I am getting the upper hand, he is loosing.  He starts to run for the arena, I am in hot pursuit waiting for my backstab to cycle for the finishing blow, the lucky little runt gets a crippling blow and I am stunned, he zones right when my stun broke.  I won, but not my a death.<br>
<br>
I had 1 bubble of health left, not bad considdering I had banded armor and no buffs, he had full fine steel, obscure and augment.  Not bad eh?<br>
<br>
Must say, that got my adrenaline pumping like a crack fiend getting his first fix of the day. <p><br>
